Add ConvoDb auth boundaries and reusable db functions

- Added `ConvoDbAuthManager.ts`, `ConvoDbPermissionBoundary.ts`, `ConvoDbInstanceMap.ts`, `convo-db-auth-schemas.ts`, and `convo-db-auth-types.ts` for JWT auth state, permission-scoped database proxies, and named database lookup.
- Updated `convo-db-lib.ts` and `convo-db-types.ts` with identity-bound permission helpers, function call convenience APIs, database names, auth managers, and named DB factory support.
- Updated `BaseConvoDb.ts`, `HttpConvoCompletionService.ts`, and DB adapter files to support auth managers, db names, schema-validated function calls, and corrected query traversal state handling.
- Updated `convo-lang-hono.ts` and added `JwtVerifiery.ts` to verify ConvoDb JWTs and wrap API database access in permission boundaries, with an option to disable db auth.
- Extended `convo.ts`, `convo-cli-types.ts`, `convo-cli-api-server.ts`, `convo-cli-db-function-loader.ts`, and `convo-cli-db-util.ts` with CLI commands for loading, querying, executing, and calling ConvoDb functions.
- Added the `db-functions` package with auth-related functions in `create-user.ts`, `init-auth.ts`, `sign-in-email-password.ts`, plus auth helpers, package metadata, tsconfig, and README documentation.
- Updated `db-map.ts`, `db-module.ts`, `BunSqliteConvoDb.ts`, `NodeSQLiteConvoDb.ts`, `InMemoryConvoDb.ts`, and `LayeredConvoDb.ts` for named database construction and updated map factory signatures.
- Added `convo-db-permission-boundary.test.ts` and updated `convo-db.test.ts` and `createTestDb.ts` to cover permission boundary behavior and db name requirements.
- Updated `index.ts` to export the new auth, permission boundary, instance map, and standard import modules.
